1
00:00:00,770 --> 00:00:03,710
(Episode 128)

2
00:00:33,410 --> 00:00:35,040
I'll hit you. Stay back.

3
00:00:41,980 --> 00:00:42,980
Boss.

4
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:45,780
Let's go.

5
00:00:50,860 --> 00:00:53,830
Is this the nurse
who was wearing the smartwatch...

6
00:00:53,890 --> 00:00:55,630
in Seo Rin's operating room?

7
00:00:55,690 --> 00:00:58,430
Yes. The hospital
where the surgery took place...

8
00:00:58,430 --> 00:00:59,930
has already closed down.

9
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,970
This woman must be hiding
somewhere right now...

10
00:01:02,970 --> 00:01:04,370
looking for a job.

11
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:07,970
Then how about we post a job opening
on a nursing recruitment site?

12
00:01:08,570 --> 00:01:09,910
I feel bad for the other applicants,

13
00:01:09,910 --> 00:01:12,380
but if we put out some bait,
you never know.

14
00:01:12,380 --> 00:01:15,780
Regular job sites require
business registration verification,

15
00:01:15,850 --> 00:01:17,250
so we can't post a fake ad.

16
00:01:17,250 --> 00:01:21,050
Besides, that nurse knows
we're looking for her,

17
00:01:21,220 --> 00:01:22,550
so she won't fall for it easily.

18
00:01:22,690 --> 00:01:25,320
So she'd never apply
to a legitimate hospital...

19
00:01:25,390 --> 00:01:26,760
because she's afraid of being exposed.

20
00:01:26,860 --> 00:01:31,560
Exactly. That's why we'll use
an underground job network.

21
00:01:31,930 --> 00:01:36,170
- That's a great idea.
- An underground job network?

22
00:01:36,300 --> 00:01:39,540
It's a place medical brokers use,
passed along through word of mouth.

23
00:01:40,240 --> 00:01:42,140
The so-called "black" clients.

24
00:01:42,670 --> 00:01:44,710
Medical staff who've had
their licenses revoked...

25
00:01:44,780 --> 00:01:46,280
or need to hide their identities...

26
00:01:46,380 --> 00:01:49,150
have a secret chatroom
where they look for jobs.

27
00:01:49,550 --> 00:01:51,980
We'll post there as if
we're looking for someone...

28
00:01:52,050 --> 00:01:55,950
to assist an illegal shadow doctor,
and set a plausible-looking trap.

29
00:01:56,390 --> 00:01:58,860
Oh my, something like that really exists?

30
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:02,860
(Staffing Services, Housekeeper)

31
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:13,570
- Manager Lee.
- Jun Ho.

32
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:16,740
You've been through a lot.

33
00:02:17,340 --> 00:02:18,340
I'm okay.

34
00:02:18,740 --> 00:02:21,180
Anyway, what about CEO Chae?
What happened to her?

35
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:23,520
I've made a plan to get her out today.

36
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:25,580
Where is she?

37
00:02:26,350 --> 00:02:27,420
At Chairman Ma's house.

38
00:02:28,350 --> 00:02:29,350
Chairman Ma's house?

39
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:36,390
Help me.

40
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:40,400
Help me.

41
00:02:41,970 --> 00:02:42,970
Help me.

42
00:02:44,570 --> 00:02:46,040
Help me.

43
00:02:48,670 --> 00:02:49,740
Help me.

44
00:02:54,180 --> 00:02:57,580
So you're finally begging for your life.

45
00:03:01,190 --> 00:03:02,590
I was going to starve you to death,

46
00:03:02,890 --> 00:03:06,060
but I'm giving you this out of pity.
So eat.

47
00:03:10,860 --> 00:03:13,300
Your life is so pathetic.

48
00:03:13,900 --> 00:03:16,670
Why do you live like this
when you have everything?

49
00:03:21,070 --> 00:03:24,840
Are you pitying me? How dare you pity me?

50
00:03:26,010 --> 00:03:27,280
Don't make me laugh, Jung Suk Hee.

51
00:03:27,980 --> 00:03:30,110
You think I'll let you all go
when I get out of here?

52
00:03:30,180 --> 00:03:32,420
- Not a chance.
- This woman is unbelievable.

53
00:03:35,390 --> 00:03:38,490
I see a little food in your system
has you acting up again.

54
00:03:38,890 --> 00:03:41,130
You'll never be a decent human being.

55
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:43,290
Do you still not realize
what you've done wrong?

56
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:46,200
If I have sinned, it's all because of you.

57
00:03:46,970 --> 00:03:49,270
If you hadn't had Dong Seok's child
in the first place,

58
00:03:49,930 --> 00:03:52,140
my son wouldn't have died in my womb.

59
00:03:52,670 --> 00:03:55,440
Then now, as my son's mother.

60
00:03:56,010 --> 00:03:58,440
I would have rightfully become
the head of Dream.

61
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:03,010
Then nothing would have happened
to either of you.

62
00:04:04,420 --> 00:04:07,920
What kind of twisted logic is that?
You killed your own son.

63
00:04:08,190 --> 00:04:10,890
You killed him when
you fell down the stairs.

64
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:12,390
That's ridiculous.

65
00:04:13,290 --> 00:04:15,990
- You started all this.
- If you keep blaming others,

66
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:19,160
- will your sins be lessened?
- Shut up.

67
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:23,400
A monster like you...

68
00:04:23,740 --> 00:04:26,070
is a woman who should have
never become a mother.

69
00:04:26,470 --> 00:04:28,210
Seo Rin died because of you...

70
00:04:28,770 --> 00:04:32,240
- and Kang Jun Ho's life will be ruined.
- Shut up.

71
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:35,210
How dare trash like you even say
my Jun Ho's name?

72
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:37,250
Do you think I can't get out of here?

73
00:04:37,750 --> 00:04:40,220
When I get out,
I'll get rid of all of you...

74
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:43,660
and put the crown of Dream on my Jun Ho.

75
00:04:44,090 --> 00:04:46,460
- Just you wait.
- Go ahead. Struggle until the end.

76
00:04:47,030 --> 00:04:50,530
You pushed me off the cliff,
and took my Seo Rin away from me.

77
00:04:50,830 --> 00:04:52,400
And you were afraid
that would be discovered,

78
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:54,000
so you killed Bok Gil.

79
00:04:54,330 --> 00:04:55,500
After doing all that,

80
00:04:55,730 --> 00:04:57,770
you should've
at least raised my Seo Rin well.

81
00:04:58,940 --> 00:05:02,570
Seo Rin still thought of you
as her mother...

82
00:05:02,570 --> 00:05:04,080
for 30 years.

83
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:08,010
Then you drove that child to her death.

84
00:05:08,580 --> 00:05:10,280
Did you want Dream that badly?

85
00:05:11,350 --> 00:05:12,520
Shut up.

86
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:16,550
You will never, ever
get your hands on Dream.

87
00:05:16,890 --> 00:05:18,260
In my name as a mother,

88
00:05:18,690 --> 00:05:21,860
- I'll make sure you pay for this.
- Hey, Jung Suk Hee.

89
00:05:22,330 --> 00:05:23,330
How dare you!

90
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:29,030
When I think of Seo Rin,
I want to kill you.

91
00:05:29,970 --> 00:05:31,870
I want to tear you to pieces.

92
00:05:33,670 --> 00:05:35,640
But for your son, Kang Jun Ho,

93
00:05:36,170 --> 00:05:37,340
you should stop here.

94
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:40,340
I'm giving you one last chance.

95
00:05:41,110 --> 00:05:43,080
If you have a shred of conscience left,

96
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:44,620
pay for your crimes.

97
00:05:45,050 --> 00:05:49,320
That's the only way Kang Jun Ho
won't have to pay for your sins.

98
00:05:50,220 --> 00:05:53,290
What did you just say?
How dare you say such awful things?

99
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:56,590
You'll end up losing Kang Jun Ho,
just like Seo Rin.

100
00:05:58,330 --> 00:05:59,930
Then you'll know...

101
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:02,730
what gut-wrenching pain feels like.

102
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,940
Will you shut up?

103
00:06:04,540 --> 00:06:05,540
How dare you!

104
00:06:10,010 --> 00:06:14,110
Hey, Jung Suk Hee.

105
00:06:14,550 --> 00:06:17,750
Jung Suk Hee, take that back!

106
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:35,530
I'm sure CEO Chae is over there.

107
00:06:45,410 --> 00:06:48,750
If the last ping from CEO Chae's phone
was at Chairman Ma's house,

108
00:06:49,250 --> 00:06:51,020
then the old, unused warehouse
in the basement...

109
00:06:51,450 --> 00:06:52,720
That must be the place.

110
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:01,790
That food made me...

111
00:07:02,690 --> 00:07:04,000
so thirsty.

112
00:07:16,610 --> 00:07:17,780
Water.

113
00:07:17,780 --> 00:07:19,010
Give me some water.

114
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:20,680
Water.

115
00:07:21,650 --> 00:07:22,810
Give me some water.

116
00:07:23,950 --> 00:07:25,520
I said, I need water.

117
00:07:27,020 --> 00:07:28,020
Water.

118
00:07:36,690 --> 00:07:37,760
Help me.

119
00:07:41,630 --> 00:07:42,800
Help me.

120
00:07:44,370 --> 00:07:45,370
Is someone there?

121
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:47,610
CEO Chae?

122
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:49,270
Is anyone there?

123
00:07:49,970 --> 00:07:51,740
- CEO Chae?
- Jun Ho?

124
00:07:51,810 --> 00:07:53,980
- CEO Chae?
- Jun Ho? Is that you, my son?

125
00:07:55,350 --> 00:07:56,350
CEO Chae?

126
00:07:56,880 --> 00:08:00,990
- Are you in there? It's me, Jun Ho.
- Jun Ho, Mom's here.

127
00:08:01,290 --> 00:08:02,850
Mom's right here, Jun Ho.

128
00:08:03,190 --> 00:08:07,530
Help me, Jun Ho.
I feel like I'm going to die.

129
00:08:07,990 --> 00:08:09,030
Hang on.

130
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:34,520
Mother.

131
00:08:36,050 --> 00:08:37,490
Jun Ho, my son.

132
00:08:40,990 --> 00:08:41,990
Mom.

133
00:08:43,330 --> 00:08:44,330
Jun Ho.

134
00:08:46,230 --> 00:08:49,170
This is the first time I've heard
my son call me Mom.

135
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,000
Jun Ho.

136
00:08:52,270 --> 00:08:54,610
You're safe now. I'm here.

137
00:08:55,610 --> 00:08:57,740
I've waited so long for you.

138
00:08:58,310 --> 00:08:59,610
We have to get out of here now.

139
00:09:00,750 --> 00:09:01,750
Okay.

140
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:07,720
Hi, Baek Ho. I just arrived.

141
00:09:08,490 --> 00:09:09,790
I'm going to check on Chae Hwa Young.

142
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:19,560
Oh Jang Mi is going in now.

143
00:09:30,410 --> 00:09:32,440
Help me.
Jang Mi is coming to the warehouse.

144
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:57,640
I think someone messed
with my car, Baek Ho.

145
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,300
I'll call you back.

146
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:00,400
Okay.

147
00:10:09,780 --> 00:10:12,820
There's a side gate behind the garden
that only the staff use.

148
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:14,350
Come out that way.

149
00:10:17,690 --> 00:10:18,690
Jun Ho.

150
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:32,070
(Ma Dae Chang)

151
00:10:48,050 --> 00:10:49,150
Come on, hurry.

152
00:10:49,750 --> 00:10:50,860
CEO Chae.

153
00:11:12,180 --> 00:11:13,610
Never trust Chairman Ma.

154
00:11:14,410 --> 00:11:17,620
Not Chairman Ma, nor his family,
Oh Jang Mi and Jung Suk Hee.

155
00:11:17,820 --> 00:11:20,790
They are all your sworn enemies.

156
00:11:23,590 --> 00:11:24,620
No.

157
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:26,720
It's just one
of Chae Hwa Young's blatant lies.

158
00:11:30,630 --> 00:11:31,630
Baek Ho.

159
00:11:34,230 --> 00:11:35,370
What happened to Hwa Young?

160
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:38,300
Is she still kidnapped?
Have you heard anything?

161
00:11:38,740 --> 00:11:39,800
I don't know either.

162
00:11:43,810 --> 00:11:44,880
Yes, Secretary Kim.

163
00:11:46,410 --> 00:11:48,950
What did you say? Lee Kang Hyuk escaped?

164
00:11:53,550 --> 00:11:54,690
Chae Hwa Young!

165
00:11:54,690 --> 00:11:56,350
How did she get out?

166
00:11:59,460 --> 00:12:03,060
- Baek Ho.
- Jang Mi, check the basement right now.

167
00:12:03,160 --> 00:12:05,600
Lee Kang Hyuk escaped from the junkyard.

168
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:07,300
Chae Hwa Young is gone too.

169
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:10,270
Lee Kang Hyuk must have broken
Chae Hwa Young out too.

170
00:12:16,910 --> 00:12:19,880
She's severely dehydrated
and malnourished.

171
00:12:20,110 --> 00:12:21,550
And she was under a lot of stress.

172
00:12:22,110 --> 00:12:25,750
She'll recover with a few days of bed rest
and some IV fluids.

173
00:12:26,150 --> 00:12:27,620
Thank you.

174
00:12:27,620 --> 00:12:28,850
Thanks again.

175
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:35,230
You should get treated too.

176
00:12:35,730 --> 00:12:37,130
You look terrible.

177
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:39,400
I'm fine.

178
00:12:43,970 --> 00:12:45,000
Mom.

179
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:46,340
Are you awake?

180
00:12:50,770 --> 00:12:51,880
Jun Ho.

181
00:12:52,780 --> 00:12:54,040
Help me up.

182
00:13:07,990 --> 00:13:08,990
You...

183
00:13:10,030 --> 00:13:11,800
Jun Ho, you saved me.

184
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:14,870
My son saved his mother.

185
00:13:16,130 --> 00:13:17,130
Thank you.

186
00:13:18,140 --> 00:13:19,640
Thank you so much, Jun Ho.

187
00:13:20,270 --> 00:13:21,640
I didn't do it alone.

188
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:25,740
Lee Kang Hyuk risked his life
to get you out.

189
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:28,350
His men helped too.

190
00:13:32,680 --> 00:13:33,920
Lee Kang Hyuk.

191
00:13:33,920 --> 00:13:35,550
How dare you betray me?

192
00:13:36,350 --> 00:13:38,890
You became Ma Dae Chang's stooge
and stabbed me in the back?

193
00:13:39,160 --> 00:13:41,060
Chairman Ma's stooge?

194
00:13:42,130 --> 00:13:44,800
You betrayed me first
and tried to frame me for everything.

195
00:13:44,930 --> 00:13:46,000
Betray you?

196
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:48,270
In that dark basement,

197
00:13:48,730 --> 00:13:52,500
I was starving like an animal,
but I never once said your name.

198
00:13:52,670 --> 00:13:54,170
What are you talking about?

199
00:13:54,770 --> 00:13:57,010
I heard you testifying myself.

200
00:13:57,210 --> 00:13:59,510
It was your voice on the phone
with Chairman Ma...

201
00:13:59,580 --> 00:14:02,010
- pinning everything on me.
- What?

202
00:14:02,010 --> 00:14:03,680
I never even spoke to Chairman Ma.

203
00:14:03,750 --> 00:14:05,220
What are you talking about?

204
00:14:05,280 --> 00:14:07,220
It sounds like you were fooled
by a voice AI.

205
00:14:07,890 --> 00:14:10,820
With deepfake technology,
mimicking someone's voice is easy.

206
00:14:12,390 --> 00:14:14,830
It looks like you both fell
for their mind games.

207
00:14:17,060 --> 00:14:19,530
I can't believe I fell
for Chairman Ma's cheap trick.

208
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:24,400
So that old fox, Chairman Ma,
decided to screw me over like this?

209
00:14:25,470 --> 00:14:27,340
Oh Jang Mi and Jung Suk Hee
won't get away with this.

210
00:14:28,610 --> 00:14:29,940
Ma Dae Chang.

211
00:14:29,940 --> 00:14:32,310
He's just sealed his own fate.

212
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:35,250
I'll never forgive them.

213
00:14:45,590 --> 00:14:48,930
Grandfather, Lee Kang Hyuk
escaped with Chae Hwa Young.

214
00:14:48,990 --> 00:14:52,660
- What do we do now?
- Contact Secretary Kim immediately.

215
00:14:53,260 --> 00:14:55,800
Tell him to search every inch of Seoul.

216
00:14:56,230 --> 00:15:00,100
They're rats in a trap.
How far can they possibly get?

217
00:15:00,700 --> 00:15:03,110
Find them immediately...

218
00:15:03,540 --> 00:15:06,280
and make them kneel before me.

219
00:15:14,550 --> 00:15:16,550
So CEO Chae wasn't on a business trip
to New York.

220
00:15:16,650 --> 00:15:18,020
The Chairman had her locked up.

221
00:15:19,890 --> 00:15:21,890
It's horrible just thinking about it.

222
00:15:21,890 --> 00:15:24,500
My darling may put on a happy face,

223
00:15:24,500 --> 00:15:27,500
but on the inside,
he's a truly terrifying and ruthless man.

224
00:15:27,770 --> 00:15:30,830
Seriously. Stop calling him darling.

225
00:15:31,140 --> 00:15:33,040
The Chairman told you
not to use that word.

226
00:15:33,170 --> 00:15:35,670
Am I not allowed
to call my husband darling?

227
00:15:35,670 --> 00:15:37,240
It's such a habit.

228
00:15:37,310 --> 00:15:39,980
How can I stop myself?

229
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:43,580
Mom, we're on the edge
of a cliff right now.

230
00:15:43,810 --> 00:15:46,680
Oh Jang Mi was promoted
to general manager overnight.

231
00:15:47,650 --> 00:15:48,650
Mom.

232
00:15:49,490 --> 00:15:52,490
This is a recorder, so keep it with you.

233
00:15:52,490 --> 00:15:54,060
If we're going to survive
these chaotic times,

234
00:15:54,060 --> 00:15:56,230
we need something like this
to protect ourselves.

235
00:15:56,330 --> 00:15:59,060
Really? It can record things?

236
00:16:00,260 --> 00:16:02,700
But how did we end up like this?

237
00:16:04,030 --> 00:16:06,700
I really want to trust my darling.

238
00:16:07,270 --> 00:16:10,540
What? Jun Ho was demoted to director?

239
00:16:11,210 --> 00:16:13,080
And Oh Jang Mi is now the general manager?

240
00:16:13,380 --> 00:16:15,350
Yes, that's the official personnel change.

241
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:17,820
Those bastards.

242
00:16:17,820 --> 00:16:18,880
Ma Dae Chang.

243
00:16:19,180 --> 00:16:21,850
So he's finally crossed a line
he never should have.

244
00:16:23,390 --> 00:16:24,660
In the end, Ma Dae Chang...

245
00:16:25,160 --> 00:16:26,860
is forcing my hand.

246
00:16:26,860 --> 00:16:29,160
Kang Hyuk, when should we set the D-day?

247
00:16:40,670 --> 00:16:42,440
This is Kang Jun Ho.

248
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:44,780
Director Kang, come to my office.

249
00:16:47,750 --> 00:16:48,910
Yes, I will.

250
00:17:00,090 --> 00:17:01,690
I'm heading
to the general manager's office.

251
00:17:06,930 --> 00:17:08,400
Did the general manager call for him?

252
00:17:08,900 --> 00:17:11,100
- Do you think something's wrong?
- I don't know.

253
00:17:11,470 --> 00:17:12,570
Do you have nothing better to do?

254
00:17:13,140 --> 00:17:15,610
Stop worrying about other people
and get back to work.

255
00:17:15,970 --> 00:17:17,880
(General Manager Ma Seo Rin)

256
00:17:18,040 --> 00:17:21,710
Jun Ho must know
where Chae Hwa Young is hidden.

257
00:17:22,350 --> 00:17:25,050
There's no way Chae Hwa Young
wouldn't have told her own son.

258
00:17:25,250 --> 00:17:28,590
He's my brother, but I can't believe
how well he hides behind that mask.

259
00:17:29,020 --> 00:17:31,220
He really is Chae Hwa Young's son.

260
00:17:31,490 --> 00:17:34,630
Grandfather had Secretary Kim
send out all of his men,

261
00:17:34,830 --> 00:17:36,660
but they still haven't found
a single trace of them.

262
00:17:37,130 --> 00:17:39,760
Maybe they've left Seoul
and are hiding in the countryside?

263
00:17:39,830 --> 00:17:41,730
No, in her condition,
she couldn't have gone far.

264
00:17:42,030 --> 00:17:43,300
She's probably in a private hospital.

265
00:17:53,140 --> 00:17:55,150
You wanted to see me, General Manager Ma?

266
00:17:55,450 --> 00:17:58,280
You know where CEO Chae is, don't you?

267
00:17:58,450 --> 00:18:00,920
Isn't CEO Chae on a business trip
in New York?

268
00:18:01,420 --> 00:18:05,220
- I'm not sure why you're asking me that.
- Stop playing dumb and tell us the truth.

269
00:18:05,720 --> 00:18:06,960
Where did you hide Chae Hwa Young?

270
00:18:08,360 --> 00:18:10,060
I have no idea what you're talking about.

271
00:18:10,730 --> 00:18:12,930
Are you saying CEO Chae isn't
on a business trip to New York?

272
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:16,430
Kang Jun Ho, you're going to be
charged as an accomplice.

273
00:18:17,870 --> 00:18:19,140
Director Kang.

274
00:18:19,140 --> 00:18:23,570
We have more than enough evidence
to put your mother in prison.

275
00:18:23,570 --> 00:18:25,110
You're just wasting time.

276
00:18:25,610 --> 00:18:27,240
Do you want to be charged
as an accomplice?

277
00:18:27,780 --> 00:18:29,010
Do whatever you want.

278
00:18:29,450 --> 00:18:31,750
When have you ever
asked for my approval before?

279
00:18:33,280 --> 00:18:35,250
If there's nothing else, I'll be going.

280
00:18:35,950 --> 00:18:37,120
I have a mountain of work to do.

281
00:18:46,060 --> 00:18:48,200
Jang Mi, you should be careful.

282
00:18:48,630 --> 00:18:52,140
Chae Hwa Young stops at nothing
to get payback...

283
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:53,440
for what's been done to her.

284
00:18:53,770 --> 00:18:57,570
- There's no telling what she'll do next.
- I know. Ever since she ran away,

285
00:18:57,640 --> 00:18:59,740
it's been way too quiet.

286
00:19:00,180 --> 00:19:02,280
That's what makes it so creepy
and unnerving.

287
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:06,820
I wonder what horrible things
she's secretly plotting.

288
00:19:09,350 --> 00:19:12,160
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

289
00:19:19,930 --> 00:19:21,170
Is that really you, Mom?

290
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:23,400
You look so different.

291
00:19:23,470 --> 00:19:26,840
Oh my goodness, it's like
we have a celebrity in the house.

292
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:29,770
I didn't know
Mom had such an elegant look.

293
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:31,710
Really?

294
00:19:32,110 --> 00:19:35,150
But Mom, where are you going today,
all dressed up?

295
00:19:35,280 --> 00:19:38,380
To the courthouse
to file a paternity suit.

296
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:40,780
Father asked me to go with him.

297
00:19:40,850 --> 00:19:42,990
He could just have the lawyers do that.

298
00:19:44,020 --> 00:19:47,290
Father said he wants to file it himself.

299
00:19:47,360 --> 00:19:51,160
Of course.
How long must he have waited for this day?

300
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:53,730
Mom, good luck.

301
00:19:54,260 --> 00:19:55,300
Okay.

302
00:20:18,960 --> 00:20:19,960
Good.

303
00:20:22,560 --> 00:20:25,260
They just finished filing
the paternity suit at the courthouse...

304
00:20:25,260 --> 00:20:26,700
and went back home.

305
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:28,630
So they finally did it.

306
00:20:29,270 --> 00:20:30,270
Got it.

307
00:20:32,300 --> 00:20:34,200
My goodness.

308
00:20:36,570 --> 00:20:37,980
How do you feel?

309
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:43,010
It feels a bit surreal.

310
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:45,980
But at the same time,
I'm finally being recognized...

311
00:20:45,980 --> 00:20:47,080
as your real daughter.

312
00:20:48,390 --> 00:20:49,890
It feels really good.

313
00:20:51,690 --> 00:20:55,460
But we already did the DNA test
and everything,

314
00:20:55,560 --> 00:20:59,100
- so why is it taking so long?
- A privately conducted DNA test...

315
00:20:59,160 --> 00:21:01,930
isn't easily admissible
as evidence in court.

316
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:05,600
So we have to get retested
at a hospital designated by the judge...

317
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:08,010
as part of a court-ordered
examination procedure.

318
00:21:08,340 --> 00:21:10,870
And then a family relations investigator
visits us in person.

319
00:21:10,970 --> 00:21:13,380
Once you factor in
the field investigation period,

320
00:21:14,010 --> 00:21:16,350
it'll take at least six months.

321
00:21:17,750 --> 00:21:19,220
I heard you studied law...

322
00:21:19,650 --> 00:21:22,590
and you explain it all so well,
my daughter.

323
00:21:22,920 --> 00:21:25,890
Strangely, I seem to remember
everything I memorized.

324
00:21:29,190 --> 00:21:30,860
Grandfather. Mom.

325
00:21:30,860 --> 00:21:32,800
- Hello.
- Chairman.

326
00:21:34,900 --> 00:21:37,770
I told them to come
so we could all eat together.

327
00:21:39,170 --> 00:21:40,200
Father.

328
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:52,320
Here.

329
00:21:54,180 --> 00:21:56,050
I've always wanted to do this.

330
00:21:56,120 --> 00:21:59,120
Putting something delicious
on my daughter's spoon.

331
00:22:00,090 --> 00:22:02,260
I wanted to do this before I die.

332
00:22:03,030 --> 00:22:05,130
Father, why would you say that?

333
00:22:06,430 --> 00:22:09,830
I'll make you grilled fish
every single day,

334
00:22:10,130 --> 00:22:14,810
- so you have to do this for me, okay?
- Of course, my dear.

335
00:22:16,610 --> 00:22:19,410
The Chairman and you, Mom, deserve
nothing but happiness from now on.

336
00:22:19,740 --> 00:22:21,480
You've both been through so much hardship.

337
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:24,680
Right, you're Tae Pyung, was it?

338
00:22:24,750 --> 00:22:26,580
Yes, Chairman.

339
00:22:27,520 --> 00:22:32,490
If you're Eun Hye's son,
then you're practically my grandson.

340
00:22:32,660 --> 00:22:36,060
- Think of me as your grandfather.
- Grandfather?

341
00:22:37,060 --> 00:22:39,860
I couldn't possibly call you...

342
00:22:40,030 --> 00:22:43,300
Of course, he's your grandfather.
I call him Grandfather too.

343
00:22:43,970 --> 00:22:44,970
Grandfather.

344
00:22:48,970 --> 00:22:51,740
Since it's such a happy occasion,
I'd like to sing a song.

345
00:22:53,980 --> 00:22:55,050
Maybe next time.

346
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:56,680
Yes, Grandfather.

347
00:22:58,280 --> 00:23:00,480
Seriously, read the room.

348
00:23:00,820 --> 00:23:03,490
- This is delicious, Grandfather.
- Good.

349
00:23:04,790 --> 00:23:07,620
(Staffing Services, Housekeeper)

350
00:23:07,620 --> 00:23:08,760
CEO Chae.

351
00:23:09,460 --> 00:23:12,500
Even so, it will take over six months
for the results to come out.

352
00:23:12,560 --> 00:23:15,370
I know,
but they went and filed it themselves?

353
00:23:15,370 --> 00:23:16,470
Is it really that urgent for them?

354
00:23:16,600 --> 00:23:18,870
We're going to take care of everything
before then anyway, aren't we?

355
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:20,670
Don't get too worked up.

356
00:23:21,340 --> 00:23:22,710
Oh, right. Chairman Ma...

357
00:23:23,770 --> 00:23:26,410
How long has it been since you
switched him to the medicine I gave you?

358
00:23:26,740 --> 00:23:27,740
Why?

359
00:23:28,610 --> 00:23:30,050
Well, it's been a while.

360
00:23:32,280 --> 00:23:33,820
Then we should be able to start now.

361
00:23:34,350 --> 00:23:35,720
What did you say that medicine was again?

362
00:23:35,990 --> 00:23:37,250
It's a powerful diuretic.

363
00:23:38,020 --> 00:23:41,220
It can cause muscle weakness
and may also induce an arrhythmia,

364
00:23:41,790 --> 00:23:42,790
so things will get quite dangerous.

365
00:23:43,260 --> 00:23:45,430
Come to think of it,
his hands have been trembling,

366
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:47,600
and he's had frequent headaches
and dizzy spells.

367
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:49,300
Even a small shock...

368
00:23:49,900 --> 00:23:52,000
will likely give us the result we want.

369
00:23:53,470 --> 00:23:56,110
- What about the medicine for Oh Jang Mi?
- I've prepared it.

370
00:23:56,570 --> 00:23:58,540
Oh, right. What about the CCTV?

371
00:23:58,840 --> 00:24:02,150
There was always a CCTV camera
between the living room and the study.

372
00:24:03,680 --> 00:24:06,550
But Chairman Ma was uncomfortable with it,
so it was turned off.

373
00:24:07,080 --> 00:24:09,520
Won't it look suspicious
if we turn it back on?

374
00:24:10,390 --> 00:24:12,120
We just have to rig the Wi-Fi.

375
00:24:12,590 --> 00:24:16,390
We'll say the Wi-Fi is spotty,
so the CCTV cuts out sometimes too.

376
00:24:16,960 --> 00:24:18,860
So it should be disconnected it
when I leave.

377
00:24:19,030 --> 00:24:20,660
It'll look suspicious
if only my connection drops,

378
00:24:20,660 --> 00:24:22,170
so we'll disconnect San Wol's too.

379
00:24:22,700 --> 00:24:26,400
The police will just think that
when the Wi-Fi is out,

380
00:24:26,470 --> 00:24:27,670
the CCTV doesn't work.

381
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:31,580
So, should we make tomorrow D-day?

382
00:24:32,310 --> 00:24:35,210
I have intel that Secretary Kim
is going out of town on business tomorrow.

383
00:24:35,350 --> 00:24:39,120
Right. And it looks like the housekeeper
went to her daughter's house,

384
00:24:40,080 --> 00:24:41,520
so we just need to get
San Wol out of the house.

385
00:24:42,020 --> 00:24:43,020
And...

386
00:24:43,790 --> 00:24:46,860
don't forget to plant a tracker
on Oh Jang Mi's car.

387
00:24:47,060 --> 00:24:48,230
Yes, understood.

388
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:51,960
Everything is perfectly in place.

389
00:24:52,430 --> 00:24:53,960
Right. Let's do this.

390
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:55,570
Jung Suk Hee, Oh Jang Mi.

391
00:24:56,430 --> 00:24:58,070
You two are finished.

392
00:25:05,980 --> 00:25:07,010
General Manager Ma.

393
00:25:08,410 --> 00:25:12,420
My mom had to go out,
and she called on her way.

394
00:25:12,650 --> 00:25:15,320
She asked me to stay with the Chairman
since he's home alone.

395
00:25:16,250 --> 00:25:17,250
Really?

396
00:25:23,230 --> 00:25:24,290
Grandfather.

397
00:25:27,060 --> 00:25:29,070
Grandfather. Are you in the study?

398
00:25:32,940 --> 00:25:34,040
Grandfather.

399
00:25:37,170 --> 00:25:39,340
Grandfather!

400
00:25:40,440 --> 00:25:42,880
Oh no. Wake up, Grandfather.

401
00:25:42,880 --> 00:25:45,250
Wait, 911...

402
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:56,890
Let go of him. Step away from the victim.

403
00:25:58,630 --> 00:25:59,900
You're police officers, right?

404
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:03,200
Please call 911 for my grandfather.
Please?

405
00:26:07,800 --> 00:26:10,770
- Why are you doing this?
- Ma Seo Rin, you are under arrest...

406
00:26:10,840 --> 00:26:13,480
for the attempted murder
of a lineal ascendant.

407
00:26:14,110 --> 00:26:18,450
You have the right to an attorney
and the right to remain silent.

408
00:26:18,520 --> 00:26:21,820
Anything you say can be used against you
in a court of law.

409
00:26:22,090 --> 00:26:24,890
What? No. It wasn't me.

410
00:26:24,890 --> 00:26:26,690
I swear it wasn't.

411
00:26:51,650 --> 00:26:53,280
(The First Man)

412
00:26:53,350 --> 00:26:55,950
It wasn't me.

413
00:26:56,090 --> 00:26:57,920
I'm a lawyer
with Dream Group's Legal Team.

414
00:26:57,990 --> 00:26:58,990
What's going on?

415
00:26:59,090 --> 00:27:01,990
Attempted murder.
We caught her red-handed.

416
00:27:02,130 --> 00:27:04,660
The trap Chae Hwa Young set
is too elaborate.

417
00:27:04,960 --> 00:27:06,860
Am I really going to prison?

418
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:10,270
I promise you. I'll get you out of here
as fast as I can, Jang Mi.

419
00:27:10,570 --> 00:27:12,770
It feels like a dream...

420
00:27:12,770 --> 00:27:16,310
having a nice, quiet family meal
at home, right, Jun Ho?

421
00:27:16,710 --> 00:27:19,480
Here's to our family's love.

422
00:27:19,980 --> 00:27:22,450
Chae Hwa Young,
laugh all you want for now.

423
00:27:22,880 --> 00:27:26,020
The day you cry tears of blood
is just around the corner.

424
00:27:28,650 --> 00:27:30,650
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
